The paper deals with indexing data structures for pattern matching in strings, trees, and graphs, which are all fundamental topics in computer science. The use of indexes and algorithms for efficient pattern matching is a common theme in many subfields of computer science, but the focus on jumbled pattern matching suggests that the paper is more likely to be categorized under data structures (cs.DS) or discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of quadratic and linear space also suggests that computational geometry (cs.CG) and information retrieval (cs.IR) may be relevant subfields. Finally, the use of approximate matches suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) may also be a relevant subfield.
